More air traffic controllers in Worms in future
The University of Applied Sciences in Worms continues to take off: The "DFS Deutsche Flugsicherung" is donating a professorship for "Air Traffic Management".
A corresponding contract between the university and DFS has now been signed in Worms.
The contract was initially concluded for three years and will start in 2021.
The professorship gives you the opportunity to start your studies not only in the summer but also in the winter semester.
This means that twice as many students can be trained as before.
At the same time, the capacities at both the university and the DFS air traffic control academy are being used evenly.
The DFS will advise the university on establishing and filling the professorship.
Represented at the university since 2019
Since the summer semester of 2019, the first students have been studying air traffic management at the University of Worms as part of their training to become air traffic controllers.
Nine students have already started this year.
So far, the experiences at DFS have been very positive, the performance of the students is excellent.
The combination of studies and pilot training makes a significant contribution to further increasing the attractiveness of the pilot profession.
"In these times, funding is not easy for us economically.
However, we firmly anticipate that air traffic will recover and grow again in the long term.
In order to be able to continue to fulfill our legal mandate in the future, we need highly qualified staff, "says Professor Klaus-Dieter Scheurle, Chairman of the DFS Managing Director when signing the contract.
"For DFS, the endowed professorship is a future-proof investment that will provide air traffic controllers with a broad, interdisciplinary knowledge base in the long term.
We are therefore continuing our good cooperation with the university and at the same time reinforcing our attractiveness as an employer ".
This is also underlined by Professor Dr. Jens Hermsdorf, President of the University of Worms: "The endowed professorship forms an important bridge between science and business.
With her, we would like to build on the already existing cooperation with DFS Deutsche Flugsicherung as a practical partner for the dual bachelor's degree in Air Traffic Management ".
The trust of the German air traffic control system is both a motivation and an obligation for the University of Worms to further develop its teaching and research skills in the future fields of air traffic.
With the first endowed professorship for a dual course of study, the university can set very special highlights and innovative focal points for its students when working for the air traffic controllers of tomorrow.
Dr. Denis Alt, State Secretary in the Ministry of Science, Further Education and Culture, emphasizes: "The University of Worms, with its focus on air traffic, has a unique selling point in Rhineland-Palatinate.
Today's signing of the cooperation agreement strengthens the profile of the university ".
